            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-1" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">a certain stranger</persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">361</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">563</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-2" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <date notBefore="0530" notAfter="0536" calendar="Gregorian">Sometime between 530 and 536, in the month of November</date>,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">a stranger</persName>came to the<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">convent outside of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/8">Amida</placeName></placeName>. Dirty and worn out,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">he</persName>stood at vespers and at table without speaking.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/poverty http://syriaca.org/keyword/vespers http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">361</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">563</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-3" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1560">Adam</persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">362</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">564</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-4" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                           In<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">the convent</placeName>,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>refused to speak to the brothers, calling himself a stranger, sinner, and son of<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1560">Adam</persName>.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/silence http://syriaca.org/keyword/sin http://syriaca.org/keyword/emotions"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">362</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">564</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-5" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            While in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">the convent</placeName><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>refused to sleep during the night while others were awake, and during service he would lie on the floor crying, leading<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">the archimandrite</persName>question him. 
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/sleep http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/silence http://syriaca.org/keyword/tears http://syriaca.org/keyword/emotions"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">363</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">565</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-6" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">the archimandrite</persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">363</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">565</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-7" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">The archimandrite</persName>approached<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>about his actions. Attending vespers,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">he</persName>began to cry because of his humility and sinfulness before God.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/tears http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasterieshttp://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monastic-heads http://syriaca.org/keyword/archimandrites http://syriaca.org/keyword/vespers"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">364</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">567</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-8" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Speaking with<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">the archimandrite</persName>,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>decided to stay in<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">the convent</placeName>for the winter.<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">He</persName>continued in his silence and weeping, garnering the appreciation of the brothers, who were encouraged by him. 
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/silence http://syriaca.org/keyword/tears http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/emotions"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">369</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">571</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-9" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            In his tears and sighs,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the blessed man</persName>prophecied that he would die in three days. While on his deathbed, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">he</persName>shared with the brothers that he had been thirty-nine years since he had taken his monastic vows, asking for their prayers and blessings.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/memory http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/silence http://syriaca.org/keyword/tears http://syriaca.org/keyword/emotions http://syriaca.org/keyword/prophecy"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">371</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">573</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/821-10" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Close to death,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the blessed man</persName>went into the vestry to pray. After a while,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">the archimandrite</persName>entered to find<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>praying on his mat, as if he was asleep. As<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">the Archimandrite</persName>spoke,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>gave up his soul to God. 
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/death http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/sleep"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">372</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">574</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
